‚Ä¢ Dress is business casual.

‚Ä¢ MASKS MUST BE WORN TO ENTER THE BUILDING!

DRISCOLL ISD PLANS FOR THE GRADUAL RETURN OF STUDENTS FOR FACE-TO-FACE INSTRUCTION IN 2020-2021!
Driscoll ISD will begin gradually transitioning students on campus for Traditional (Face-to-Face) learning beginning next week. Parents will be asked to select Remote Learning or Traditional Learning for each child in their household. Those wishing to attend school on campus may do so according to the following schedule:
Monday, August 17th ‚Äì Pre-Kindergarten and Kindergarten students selecting Traditional Learning may return to campus,
Monday, August 24th ‚Äì 1st and 3rd grade,
Monday, August 31st ‚Äì 4th and 6th grade,
Monday, September 8th ‚Äì 2nd and 7th grade and
Monday September 14th ‚Äì 5th and 8th grade
Surveys will be sent via School Messenger one week prior to each grade levels‚Äô return date. Parents are asked to select Remote Learning (At-Home) or Traditional (Face-2-Face) learning at school. Please be sure to complete the survey as soon as possible so that we can properly prepare for an accurate number of students on campus each week.

ATTENTION PARENTS!!!
If your child was denied P-EBT benefits, the attached documents may assist you in receiving those funds. Contact HHSC at 883-613-6220 or at AES_PEBT_Complaints@hhsc.state.tx.us and file a complaint stating that your child(ren) was denied in error. Driscoll ISD will be handing out meals twice a week on Mondays & Thursdays starting tomorrow (March 30th) from 11:00-1:00 at our bus loop curbside location! Monday meals will include 3 days worth of food for Monday, Tuesday & Wednesday and the remaining meals will be available for pickup on Thursday.
Please let us know if you plan to come so we can pre-bag or box your meals by family! Kids do not have to be with parents when they come to pick up.

You may also drop off any completed work when picking up meals, just be sure to use the labeled zip lock bag. If you don‚Äôt have the bag, please label work by name, grade and teacher for easy sorting!

Thank you and Stay Healthy!!

post_text:
Congratulations to our very own, Ms. Patricia G. Reyes for publishing her book, Teach Them to See Hearts!

After experiencing the loss of her husband a couple of years ago, Ms. Reyes began spotting hearts in unexpected places. Knowing it was him sending his love to her and their children, she photographed and cataloged each heart that she found and began spreading that love by showing our students in Driscoll how to see them as well. Before long, every child fervently searched and found hearts for Ms. Reyes to photograph. Through her journey, she has found hope, joy, and a renewed sense of peace.

Ms. Reyes‚Äô book, Teach them to see Hearts, was just released on Amazon. There is a Kindle version and paperback version. She even has a book signing at Half Price Books Saturday, March 7th from 12:00 to 3:00pm.

Congratulations, Ms. Reyes! We are so proud of you!!!!

Your message will resonate within us for years to come!

post_text:
TEXAS HONOR ROLL

Driscoll Elementary and Middle School is proud to be named a 2018 - 2019 Texas Honor Roll school for our high achievement in student success. As one of only 855 public schools in Texas, Driscoll Elementary and Middle School has been recognized for consistently demonstrating high levels of student academic achievement, improvement in achievement levels over time and reducing the achievement gaps among student populations. Because of our accomplishment, we will be featured on ERP's Honor Roll website at www.edresults.org. (Educational Results Partnership).
Congratulations Dragons and let's keep up the great work!!!

BREAKING NEWS!!!
Today we received Algebra 1 EOC (End of Course) scores for the 20 8th graders in Mrs. Judi Gonzalez‚Äôs Algebra 1 class!
For the first time in Dragon history 100% of the students not only passed the EOC test, but they all passed at the highest standard in Texas! Yep! All 20 students met the MASTERS standard on the Algebra 1 EOC test!!!
Congratulations to Mrs. Gonzalez and her 8th grade Alg 1 class! You guys are the Best of the Best!!!

post_text:
Congratulations to former Driscoll Dragon 2nd Lieutenant Quartermaster Rhonda Zuniga! On January 15, 2019, Rhonda graduated from Army Boot Camp in Fort Jackson, South Carolina, and then on April 15, 2019, she graduated from Army OCS, in Fort Benning, Georgia.
Rhonda is currently in Fort Lee Virginia for the next four months before being stationed in Washington state. Rhonda is the daughter Rudy and Lala Zuniga. Congratulations Rhonda! You continue to make us Dragon Proud!!!
